{
  "stem": "11179.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it turned out, luckily, nothing happened There was a-- there was a-- a-- a-- a-- one man stopped this kind of lynching mob, luckily.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Chinese police were in back.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They won't get involved with foreigners.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they knew darn well that those two Russian had done evil things.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it was all over after-- after they came, a man that was pretty well liked, a big man, and said, you better go home.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Nothing has changed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And sure enough, the Japanese police was back within a few hours.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we didn't know anything till-- what was over, just rumors, till the second atomic bomb was dropped.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then the news, as-- as you may know, the-- the-- the Emperor of Japan ended the war after the second bomb.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So it-- it took a while between the first and second bomb.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "After that, we-- for another six weeks, we-- we got some information.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There were some leaflets dropped, I believe from American planes, to-- to give us hope and so on, basically.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But-- but even the news media, what was available there, told us too.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "There were still-- the last few weeks, the Russians were involved in the war.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But there was-- there were, by that time, the news media was strictly-- what we heard was it was either Japanese or German.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But they didn't keep it too much of a secret.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I-- the details I forgot.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The fact was, there was a deal made with the Japanese for the next six weeks to keep it-- to stay in the city and keep law and order, which they did.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Meanwhile, the Japanese-- mean-- meanwhile, everybody had a ball in Shanghai because the Japanese did open their warehouses to-- to the Chinese employees.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
